{"key":"processedPost-16105636","value":{"id":16105636,"first":16103561,"last":16105636,"when":1334757297,"utime":"04/18/12 04:54 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Dazed Belief said:</b><br />doesnt matter how far it is off the floor <br />just want it up so water cant sit on bottom <br /></blockquote><br /><br />This is flat-out wrong.&nbsp; The terrarium needs to be sitting up on a table, at least a couple of feet off the floor.&nbsp; 90% of all contaminants in a room are floating around in the last foot or so.&nbsp; Never have a terrarium near the floor.<br /><br />For the rest of the OP questions, 6500K lamp on a 12/12 schedule, and place it only a few inches away from the terrarium so the light is very bright.&nbsp; Never run a ceiling fan in a room with a shotgun terrarium.&nbsp; Leave a window slightly open at all times.<br />RR","title":"Re: SGFC on blocks?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}